        public static dagger.ObjectGraph create(MortarScope parent,

      • requireActivityScope

        @Deprecated
public static MortarScope requireActivityScope(MortarScope parentScope,
                                          Blueprint blueprint)
        Deprecated. This method is provided to ease migration from earlier releases, which coupled Dagger and Activity integration. Instead build new scopes with MortarScope.buildChild(), and bind ObjectGraphService and BundleServiceRunner instances to them.
        Returns the existing MortarScope scope for the given Activity, or uses the Blueprint to create one if none is found. The scope will provide BundleService and BundleServiceRunner.

        It is expected that this method will be called from Activity.onCreate(android.os.Bundle). Calling it at other times may lead to surprises.

        See Also:
        MortarScope.Builder#withService(String, Object)

      • requireChild

        @Deprecated
public static MortarScope requireChild(MortarScope parentScope,
                                  Blueprint blueprint)
        Deprecated. This method is provided to ease migration from earlier releases, which required Dagger integration. Instead build new scopes with MortarScope.buildChild(), and bind ObjectGraphService instances to them.
        Returns the existing child whose name matches the given Blueprint's Blueprint.getMortarScopeName() value. If there is none, a new child is created based on Blueprint.getDaggerModule(). Note that Blueprint.getDaggerModule() is not called otherwise.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if this scope has been destroyed
        See Also:
        MortarScope.Builder#withService(String, Object)
